T1  - Efficient estimation of income distribution parameters
AU  - Kloek, Teun
AU  - van Dijk, Herman K.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 8
IS  - 1
SP  - 61
EP  - 74
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/08/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(78)90090-8
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407678900908
AB  - The parameters of several families of distributions are estimated by means of minimum χ2; use is made of random samples taken from Dutch income-earning groups in 1973. The numerical search routine used, is the Complex method due to Box. The χ2 function is evaluated by standard numerical integration procedures. The lognormal and the Gamma families are rejected because of a poor fit. The log t and the log Pearson IV families are introduced. This results in a considerable improvement of χ2 critical levels. The generalized Gamma and the Champernowne function describe the income distribution reasonably well in some cases.
ER  - 

