UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407678900854
AB  - This paper generalizes the Box and Cox (1964) procedure for the case in which the disturbances follow a first-order autoregressive process. The Box and Cox autoregressive procedure is then used to simultaneously test for autocorrelation and functional form. With the aid of some illustrative examples it is shown that corrective procedures for either misspecification taken alone may be inappropriate.
