AB  - In the paper we extend the theory of identifiability of linear dynamic models with autocorrelated errors to the case of cross-equation restrictions: We consider global identifiability in the case of affine cross-equation restrictions and local identifiability in the case of continuously differentiable cross-equation restrictions. Throughout the whole paper a minimality assumption is used.
